<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 0px 269px 624px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss b174ef864cda601f37d52e9ca06b1dc7-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Rectangular Shaped Ducts and Fittings</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>These elements should be measured by the surface area, in square meters or feet (as illustrated in Figure 16) in any project phase.&nbsp;</p>
<p>There are BIM authoring tools that natively provide this area for ducts, however, in cases where this information is not natively available, such as for duct fittings, new parameters must be introduced to calculate and report these areas.<img src="https://private.lodplanner.com/projects/11696/plan-content/1700590273101_f4173dbd-6d8b-4b78-8673-6ca39a92650a.png?Expires=1768831279&amp;Signature=WGxUytCuCQOeuTfpKiyDVQU6~FVN0hNDgh6U545Tjae0DkXBsd7vbVictha8Jn-rNmAS~IZeLy90DXgja3fGLhm7YSIfJ8Fh1KAqM8qjjgkMEbf420QYKAk~ZekBMGG9DffXzQz9Fd3FurAG1s062TyvFKatjSC9oMb5bjaHtukMDmf9vNlGZVJxZjy2fJtGiAgyYGTIk5fsN4VxSJTMGCUveFiZVZ7uJcmNT2bmBTrHtezWyBGb0dA0hUUYmhdR9Uq0l4oXz~erbwq1GLGanp~hwznSoaCyRrqiO0TPn-nU7sJcOnUBP3dLlpFMUbY~gR-ybHXAYbAA4oWO9FQdOA__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAJRIVA6WNZT4BZJPQ" class="fr-fic fr-dii" id="isPasted"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>&nbsp;Figure 16 - Illustration of the quantified surface area of ducts and fittings.</em>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><br></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">In the case of ducts with insulation or fire protection, it is necessary to consider them as a distinct typology from the regular ducts.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Any specific characteristics in the composition of these elements should result in a new element type/class, enabling more accurate and detailed quantity takeoff.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>